This paper is about optimizing the hyperparameters of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on gradient-based meta-optimization, which is a subfield of optimization and machine learning. The paper also discusses experiments on standard benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
